# Authentication & Authorization Patterns

## Authentication Methods
1. **Email/Password:** Traditional authentication via [convex/services/auth.ts](mdc:convex/services/auth.ts)
2. **Facebook OAuth:** Social login with NextAuth.js in [app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts](mdc:app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts)
3. **Guest Mode:** Persistent guest sessions for browsing without registration

## User Roles & Access Control
- **Client:** Regular customers - can browse, purchase, make reservations
- **Admin:** Store management - inventory, order processing, user management
- **Super Admin:** Full system access - user role management, system settings

## Route Protection (middleware.ts)
```typescript
- /auth/* - Public authentication routes
- /admin/* - Admin role required
- /control_panel/* - Admin or Super Admin required
- /client/* - Authentication required (redirects to login)
```

## Session Management
- **NextAuth.js:** Handles OAuth and session persistence
- **Zustand Store:** Client-side auth state with localStorage in [store/auth.ts](mdc:store/auth.ts)
- **Guest Sessions:** Auto-generated guest IDs for non-authenticated users

## Key Files
- [middleware.ts](mdc:middleware.ts) - Route protection and authorization
- [store/auth.ts](mdc:store/auth.ts) - Client-side auth state management
- [hooks/useAuth.ts](mdc:hooks/useAuth.ts) - Authentication utilities
- [app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts](mdc:app/api/auth/[...nextauth]/route.ts) - NextAuth configuration

## Important Rules
- Always check authentication state before accessing protected routes
- Support both authenticated users and guests in all features
- Use role-based access control for admin functions
- Maintain guest session persistence across page reloads